gghstats is a self-hosted GitHub repository traffic dashboard and CLI.
It stores views, clones, and related metrics in SQLite beyond GitHub's
14-day API window.

Features:
- Web UI with optional i18n (EN, ES, DE, FR, PT-BR)
- Prometheus metrics and optional README badges
- Configurable repo filter and sync interval
- Static binary (modernc SQLite), MIT licensed

WWW: https://github.com/hrodrig/gghstats
